A Chinese court has sentenced two US citizens to  prison terms of 20 and 14 years for their part in a major fraud case,  involving letters of credit totalling some 10 billion dollars, Xinhua said  Friday.
Hung Moy and Raymond Lee, both Chinese-Americans were sentenced to 20 and  14 years respectively by a court in the northern province of Hebei, the  official news agency said.
A local Agricultural Bank of China official was sentenced to 11 years for  "revealing state secrets" as part of the swindle.
